Stoll returned a 2-year $TSLA lease on 9/24/18. The sales agent quoted him a cheap price for a new 3 year 15k mile annual lease. Stoll never signed any paperwork, but gave his credit card # which the agent used to charge a $2.5k deposit.

On 10/2/18 Stoll called $TSLA about his order and was told the lease cost would be much higher. At that point he demanded his deposit back, but as of the filing on 10/10/18 it was not returned. He is suing for exemplary & punitive damages of $90k.
